Simple Perceptron Algorithm by Yan Mu
Description
This function implements a simple perceptron algorithm.
Usage
Simple_Percetron<-function(dataset, data_rate=0.7,learning_rate = 0.01, initial_vector=c(-2,3,1), loopNum = 10)
Arguments
dataset	The data that is functioned to the algorithm
data_rate	The data_rate for training set. Default value is 0.7 if not specified.
learning_rate	Learning rate of the algorithm. Default value is 0.01 if not specified
initial_vector	The initial_vector for the algorithm. Default value is c(-2,3,1)
loopNum	The times that this algorithm need to be looped.
Value
weight_vector	Final updated weight vector values.
3D image	This image shows the 3d classifications of the dataset.
2D image	This image shows the 2d classifications of the dataset.
Accuracy	The accuracy of the algorithm.
Note
This function needs to install library: rgl.
Author(s)
Yan Mu, Texas Tech University. Email: yan.mu@ttu.edu
Examples
dataset <-read.csv("F:/data.csv")
data_rate<-0.7
learning_rate<-0.01
initial_vector<-c(-2,3,1)
loopNum<-10

Simple_Percetron(dataset, data_rate,learning_rate, initial_vector, loopNum)
or
Simple_Percetron(dataset)

"The final weight vector is:"
-2.0727282  2.9365281  0.9378504
"The accuracy of the algorithm is: "
0.9666667
